#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc:4
msgid ""
"To see the documentation for a specific ufunc, use `info`.  For example, "
"``np.info(np.sin)``.  Because ufuncs are written in C (for speed) and linked "
"into Python with NumPy's ufunc facility, Python's help() function finds this "
"page whenever help() is called on a ufunc."
msgstr ""

